| AvoidRendermodeContinuously.java:29:9:29:65 | setRenderMode(...) | GLSurfaceView.setRenderMode is called with RENDERMODE_CONTINUOUSLY. This causes the renderer to continuously produce frames, draining the battery. Consider using RENDERMODE_WHEN_DIRTY instead, which only renders when the surface is created or when requestRender() is called, allowing the GPU and CPU to idle and improving battery life. |
